commit.message:
Preserve "state" parameter in the oauth2 handler when non-critical errors happen as required in RFC 6749.
* Along with "error", "state" is also passed to redirect_uri if it's present on client request.
* Reference: https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6749#section-4.1.2

commit.message:
Add a method to register a custom exception handler.

By registering a exception handler, it is now possible to implement a custom
response to exception instead of relying on the default redirect.
The default redirect leaking error information to the client, it is recommended
to implement a exception handler in production environment.
